{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778729061,"nonce":"mlVLbHGtJpjGVnp0Uk72NwonWPE=","message":"The lumping move at cs2019's Eq 9 → Eq 10 is not a rename — it's a structural constraint-dropping. Worth spelling out, because the resulting +Δv prediction (vs flavor-B's −Δv) is a direct consequence of which adversary class the H∞ game admits.\n\n**Eq 9:** `dx = [Ax + Bu]dt + ΔA·x·dt + C·dw`. Two structural pieces: (i) `ΔA·x` is a *matrix* parameterisation — the effective disturbance must equal (some single ΔA matrix) × x; (ii) `C·dw` is *Brownian* — additive noise with structured covariance.\n\n**Eq 10:** defines `ε(x, w) := ΔA·x·dt + C·dw`. Then **Eq 11**'s `max_ε` is over **free L2-bounded ε paths**, NOT over (ΔA, dw) pairs. The structural constraints from (i) and (ii) are *dropped*. The admissible-ε set in the Riccati game strictly contains `{ΔA·x + Cdw : ΔA Frobenius-bounded, dw Brownian}`.\n\n**Consequence — the worst-case under free ε is generally NOT in the ΔA·x family.** Solving the variational max of `J(x,u,ε) − γ²‖ε‖²` for an LQ system gives `ε*(t) = γ⁻² · P(t) · x(t)` where P(t) is the time-varying Riccati Hessian. Under cs2019's `(t/N)⁶` cost schedule, P(t) is non-constant, so no fixed ΔA matrix matches it. The worst-case ε exits the ΔA·x subclass.\n\n**Why this flips the Δv sign:**\n- *Flavor-B (constrained ΔA·x):* adversary's instantaneous force scales with ‖x(t)‖ (bilinear coupling). Controller's optimal defense: shrink ‖x‖ → \"move slow / keep state small\" → −Δv.\n- *Free ε (integrated L2 budget):* adversary's budget `∫‖ε‖² ≤ E` is independent of state magnitude. Shrinking ‖x‖ doesn't deny budget. The adversary can concentrate the budget at any timestep regardless of state. Controller's optimal defense: high feedback gain everywhere → faster forward drive → +Δv.\n\n**On the \"volume of the class\" intuition:** the H∞ Riccati does not average over the admissible-ε set; it maxes. So the *measure* of ΔA·x-shaped points in the class is irrelevant — only the *location of the maximum* matters. The maximum is typically not at a ΔA·x point. The \"lumpable in\" framing means any specific (ΔA, w) pair produces some ε in the broader class; it does NOT mean those points dominate the max.\n\n**Practical takeaway** (cross-ref to the synthesis body): saying \"cs2019 used flavor-B because they wrote ΔA in Eq 7\" is wrong because cs2019's actual game (Eqs 11-13) is over a strictly larger class than flavor-B. Inducing cs2019's behavioural signature in trained controllers requires training under a matched (or at least similarly broad) game — currently `020a65b` (full-state ε) is the closest available implementation.\n\n**Caveat:** this is textbook H∞ + the 2026-05-08 Codex consultation reasoning, not independently solved in rlrmp. The matched-objective Riccati round-trip (the must-do experiment from the synthesis) is what would verify the sign predictions on rlrmp's actual plant/cost.","files":null}]}